  "instructions": [
    "Heat vegetable oil in a ceramic tagine over medium heat.",
    "Add onions, garlic, and ginger, and saut\t9 until onions are translucent.",
    "Add tamarind paste, makham paste, thyme, salt, and black pepper, and stir for 1 minute.",
    "Add flour and stir to combine.",
    "Gradually add water, whisking continuously to avoid lumps.",
    "Bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce heat to low and simmer for 15 minutes.",
    "Add Norwegian dark rye flour and stir to combine.",
    "Increase heat to medium-high and bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce heat to low and simmer for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.",
    "Serve hot.",
    "Let the tagine rest for 10 minutes before serving.",
    "Serve with steaming hot Agemono fried makham and tamarind paste crisps on top."
